  <bpmn:collaboration id="Collaboration_ConcertTicketWatcher">
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_User" name="User" processRef="Process_User" />
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_ConcertTicketWatcherSystem" name="Concert ticket watcher system" processRef="Process_ConcertTicketWatcherSystem" />
    <bpmn:participant id="Participant_Invitee" name="Invitee" processRef="Process_Invitee" />
    <bpmn:messageFlow id="Flow_16g5m3m" sourceRef="ThrowEndEvent_InvitationResult" targetRef="SubProcess_SendInvitations" />
    <bpmn:messageFlow id="Flow_0lfp6kd" sourceRef="SubProcess_SendInvitations" targetRef="CatchStartEvent_Invitee" />
    <bpmn:messageFlow id="Flow_0u40nk4" sourceRef="ThrowEvent_SystemStart" targetRef="CatchStartEvent_ConcertTicketWatcherSystem" />
    <bpmn:messageFlow id="Flow_1qiwum4" sourceRef="ThrowEvent_ConcertAnnounced" targetRef="CatchEvent_WaitForConcertAnnounced" />
    <bpmn:messageFlow id="Flow_0hnj69t" sourceRef="ThrowEvent_InvatationResult" targetRef="CatchEvent_WaitForInvitationResult" />
    <bpmn:messageFlow id="Flow_1tdeh3f" sourceRef="ThrowEvent_UserReply" targetRef="CatchEvent_WaitForUserReply" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_1n3dpcw">
      <bpmn:text>artistName: string
email: string
maxDistanceKm: integer
budgetChf: integer
isGoing: boolean

invitees: list&lt;invitee&gt; [
    isGoing: boolean
    camundaUsername: string
    email: string
]</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0lq8ptf">
      <bpmn:text>table: event_watch
{
    id: PK
    ticketmaster_event_id: string
    allready_notified: boolean
}</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_1veqmjy">
      <bpmn:text>Triggers the Java worker to periodically pull the Ticketmaster API for ticket availability. Once tickets are almost available, an email notification including the purchase link is sent to the user and all invitees who requested a reminder.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_1j7peb9">
      <bpmn:text>Polls the Ticketmaster API for upcoming events matching the watched artist. Fetches user preferences from the database and filters results by maximum distance and budget. Notifies the user if a matching event is found.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0ffuv9b">
      <bpmn:text>Camunda form where the user confirms if there going to the concert and and optionally invites others by entering Camunda usernames comma-separated. The forum has validation, that ensures invitees are only addable if the user is attending. Invalid or unregistered usernames are silently skipped during processing.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_07sv779">
      <bpmn:text>This sub-process runs once for every invited person at the same time. Each invited person gets a task in their Camunda inbox where they can say yes or no. How that works on the invitee side is shown in the Invitee pool at the bottom of the diagram. The main process only continues once everyone has responded.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_09h7iwf">
      <bpmn:text>If the backend ever runs into a exidental error, this is here for the token to not eternaly go on. Also the backend will intentionally cause a error for situations like that a worker has been waiting since 50 years for a concert to happen.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_12vnafx">
      <bpmn:text>---------------------------
Generall Information
---------------------------

A second version of this BPMN diagram exists without comments for a cleaner view.

# Diagram conventions #
Blue colored elements represent data flow within the system, including database interactions and process variables. Orange colored elements are comments and detailed explanations of how individual tasks function.

# Architecture #
This project consists of three layers. A Camunda BPM engine handling process orchestration, a Java backend acting as the external task worker, and a PostgreSQL database for persistant data storage.

# Technical debt &amp; limitations #
As this is a school project, several deliberate simplifications were made that would not be normal in production. These are documented as technical debt throughout the diagram. Here some:
* The entire system runs on a single machine (including invitees). Multi-machine communication is not supported.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_137xhfd">
      <bpmn:text>Validates each entered username against the Camunda identity service. Invalid or unknown usernames are silently skiped. Then it saves the clean list as process variable inviteeList for the multi-instance sub-process to continue working with it.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_1dcjhvz" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="TextAnnotation_07sv779" targetRef="Participant_Invitee" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0j6ckmy">
      <bpmn:text>The user enters the name of the artist they want to get notifed if they have a concert. You can also fill in personal preferences, like how far the concert can be and what your budget is.

Note: the artist name must match exactly how Ticketmaster identifies the artist. The user types it in as free text. Typos or slight name variations will result in no events being found, with no feedback given to the user. This is a known technical debt.</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_0guf89o" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="TextAnnotation_0ffuv9b" targetRef="UserTask_FillInConcertSettingsForum" />
    <bpmn:association id="Association_1a0rbtb" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="TextAnnotation_137xhfd" targetRef="ServiceTask_ValidateAndResolveInviteeUsernames" />
    <bpmn:association id="Association_0yu9lvm" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="ServiceTask_FetchEventsFromAPI" targetRef="TextAnnotation_1j7peb9" />
    <bpmn:association id="Association_14qcl4k" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="ErrorBoundaryEvent_ProgramFails-FetchEventsFromAPI" targetRef="TextAnnotation_09h7iwf" />
    <bpmn:association id="Association_0or1u4f" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="TextAnnotation_07sv779" targetRef="SubProcess_SendInvitations" />
    <bpmn:association id="Association_0x1nqe8" associationDirection="None" sourceRef="TextAnnotation_1veqmjy" targetRef="ServiceTask_FetchTicketAvailabilityAndSendEmail" />
  </bpmn:collaboration>
  <bpmn:process id="Process_User" isExecutable="true" camunda:historyTimeToLive="18250">
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_1rdlhyb" sourceRef="UserTask_StartNewArtistWatch" targetRef="ThrowEvent_SystemStart" />
